{{Top|leg}}
A '''Wrodian carpet''' was an opulent style of carpet that contained rich colors arranged in a distinctive weave. Any single Wrodian carpet would be woven over the course of generations before it was finally complete.

[[Klaus Vandangante/Legends|Klaus Vandangante]] decorated the office of his mobile base with Wrodian carpets.

==Behind the scenes==
The unlicensed roleplaying magazine article "[[Twinkle, Twinkle Little Star, How I Wonder Where We Are]]", which was published without [[Lucas Licensing]] approval and thus is considered non-canon,<ref name="Unlicensed">{{UnlicensedStatus}}</ref> attributes the "[[Wrodi system/Legends|Wrode system]]" to [[Brian Daley]]'s ''[[Han Solo at Stars' End]]''
which was the first source to mention "Wrodian carpet",<ref name="HSaSE">''[[Han Solo at Stars' End]]''</ref> and places the system in [[Zebitrope sector]].<ref name="VSF13">{{VoyagesCite|13|Twinkle, Twinkle Little Star, How I Wonder Where We Are}}</ref>

